HEADWORD: Decussation
<hw>De`cus*sa"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>decussatio</ets>.]</ety> <def>Act of crossing at an acute angle, or
state of being thus crossed; an intersection in the form of an X;
<as>as, the <ex>decussation</ex> of lines, nerves, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decussative</ent>⟦br⟧
